               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> He saw most if not all of the invoice which came into my office—I cannot swear that he saw this particular one, but he saw the majority of the invoice from Smithson, and he suggested to me that he should borrow some money on the goods represented by it, and I believe I had the benefit of it—I sold some of the goods myself to regular customers.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Re-examined.</hi> There was no banking account expect in the name of Michell, and all the money went into his account at the St. James's Bank, and was paid out again except a small balance of about 70<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. (<hi rend="italic">The</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
