                  <hi rend="smallCaps">J.J. KEIGHLEY</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Re-examined</hi>). I showed the sample to Michell, and has a conversation with him before the order was sent—these two memor<lb></lb>anda of December 2nd and 6th are my clerk's writing—this letter (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) is in Michell's writing. (<hi rend="italic">This was from Michell to W.H. Wood, and <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLAY</hi> objecting to it, it was not read.</hi>)</p>
